{
  "stem": "2118.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I used to go along and I had to hold, let's say, a piece of metal right here [INAUDIBLE] or something or whatever he did.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Or-- so this is what I did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then the ghetto got organized.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We used to joke about it that they, in a year, the ghetto is going to run like a clock, on clockwork, that perfect.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it ran like clockwork.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And everybody was slowly forced to go and work into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "As more things got worse, you couldn't buy things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Then they started rationing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And if we didn't have, let's say, a card-- you didn't have a job, you couldn't get a rationing card.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Everybody had to register and have a Kennkarte card, which means an identification card.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So they knew exactly how many people there was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they took your name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They took what-- oh, you have any trade or you didn't have a trade, how old you are, and all that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And-- and we had a newspaper coming out, the [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Ghettozeit. ?] Not for too long because they ran out of paper.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Of course, it had no news outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "What was-- it tells you how to do certain things, how to try to cut corners, and advice things, or things which were happening.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Like you had to come here, you had to come there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "You have to register this or register that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You had to give up, let's say, [INAUDIBLE] or jewelry or a radio if somebody had, or guns, or you had to turn in.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They tell you where to go, what to do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Then they started putting out proclamations on-- on the street.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "In the beginning, if I remember right, they were in three languages-- Polish, German, and Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
